HEADWORD: Menispermine
<hw>Men`i*sper"mine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧nispermine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
alkaloid distinct from picrotoxin and obtained from the cocculus indicus
(the fruit of <spn>Anamirta Cocculus</spn>, formerly <spn>Menispermum
Cocculus</spn>) as a white, crystalline, tasteless powder; -- called
also <altname>menispermina</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

